form_values.2d29:
Watching brief of excavation for new build footings. Checking for knotweed rhizome in waste arisings. Assessing need for root barrier installation. 

No rhizome was seen in the arisings or in the faces of the newly cut trench. 
Since the treatment programme started, no knotweed growth has been seen in the garden in the area near to the new build footprint.  
The footings trench is outside the risk area.
Stockpiled waste arisings were inspected for the presence of knotweed rhizome and none was found.
No rhizome was found on inspecting the ground within and around the new build footprint.
Taking the above into account there is no need for a root barrier to be installed along the footings line or between the footings and the site boundary.

e77c.caption: Trenches and arisings were inspected. No knotweed rhizome seen.
Stockpiled arisings were inspected. No knotweed rhizome seen.
The drain along the side of the property was re-inspected - no regrowth seen.
